<br />
Smeagol with his secrets and the answer comes from the ring! What more can we ask for? AHEM.<br />
<br />
Now to the real strategy section<br />
<br />
Why smeagol as ring bearer?<br />
<br />
Well first of all , its a great pick :]<br />
After the first look he seems kinda bad , cse you have to sack a unbound = Play Ringbound Rangers then duh !<br />
<br />
He gives the ability to them to dual move like a train , bein able to discard minions for a mere 2 burdens.<br />
<br />
He starts off with a 7 resistance , which isn&#39;t bad :]<br />
<br />
Now let&#39;s see what else is in the deck?<br />
<br />
Alot of wouding , via mablung , the smeagol wouding cards , the forts , etc etc.<br />
The newest adition is hardy garison which is a bomb card in combination with the smeagol wounder.<br />
In one simple card u can 3 wounds , how nice is that?<br />
<br />
Elrond and Might are there for the occasional heals , and what are they fences off evil trolls or Sauron even if u like :=].<br />
<br />
U can even prepare for a tripple move using Secret  Paths.<br />
<br />
The Minion side is a casual corsair using also the  <br />
power of the new Corsair Brute , who is in my opinion very very evil in combo with red wrath.<br />
3 wounds for one minion , how nice is that? :]<br />
<br />
There are still some questionable cards in , like 3 wretches and the phial of galadriel , but its a starting concept and i&#39;d like good feedback to use it on the next big events.<br />
<br />
Enjoy!<br />
<br />
